    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "db54b269_5103d5c3",
        "filename": "golden/modules/corpus-selector-sk/corpus-selector-sk_test.js",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 110,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-18T17:40:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you.\n\nRegarding adding something to handle the selected li:\n- Currently the test relies on the \"selected\" class, which is needed to style the selected li.\n- The point of go/tott/594 is to use user-facing properties to select elements in tests, as this makes tests less brittle.\n- But as long as we\u0027re using a CSS class to style the selected li, the only way the test would break is if I rename the \"selected\" CSS class to something else, which is unlikely to happen, and I forget to update the tests.\n- Thus I\u0027m leaning towards leaving it as-is.\n\nThat said, go/tott/594 recommends against adding ARIA tags to support tests, and recommends using e.g. a data- attribute instead. So one possible alternative would be to add a \"data-selected\" attribute to the selected li, and use li[data-selected] { ... } in the style sheet instead of the current li.selected { ... }.\n\nThoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "07f5eaa4_d69095f1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 110,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 110,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "8d719b1fbeb53c7f9b9184496d2ee1706d9ab78f",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e9329ff8_b1f591d5",
        "filename": "golden/modules/corpus-selector-sk/corpus-selector-sk_test.js",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 110,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-19T12:49:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree with your recommendation of leaving it as is.\n\nIf accessibility does become a higher priority down the road as our audience scales up, we\u0027ll have to add several tags anyway; might be worth it to add as we go instead of having to come back to it, but I\u0027ll leave that decision up to you whether that\u0027s in-scope or not.",
      "parentUuid": "db54b269_5103d5c3",
